  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>There are several reasons why you might need to update your staff Username or PIN/password for logging into RepairQ. Whether you've forgotten your credentials, need to enhance security, or are simply updating account details, our software makes the process straightforward.</p><p>Users with the <strong>Manager</strong> role or higher can assist in updating these credentials directly within RepairQ. Alternatively, staff members can use the <strong>Password Reset</strong> option on the login screen to securely update their password without assistance.</p><h3 id=\"StaffManagement:UpdateYourUsernameandPassword-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1929379890\" rel=\"nofollow\">Staff Management: Add and Deactivate Staff Profiles</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1928921099\" rel=\"nofollow\">Getting Started: Login and User Profile Management</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1936785488\" rel=\"nofollow\">Staff Management Resources (with Video)</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1928986634\" rel=\"nofollow\">Getting Started: Clock In/Out of RepairQ</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"680\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1929248790/Instructional%20-%200091cd.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"StaffManagement:UpdateYourUsernameandPassword-ChangeYourUsernameandPassword\">Change Your Username and Password</h2><p /><p>A user with an Admin or Manager role will need to log into RepairQ. On the Navigation Bar, go to <strong>Staff</strong> \u2192 <strong>View Staff</strong>. On the Staff Overview page, locate the user that needs changes made. Under the Actions column, click <strong>Edit</strong>.</p><p><strong>Note:</strong> If you are working with a large number of users, there are filters on the left column of the Staff Overview page to locate a specific Staff Member.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Update Password 1.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1929248790/Update%20Password%201.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Update Password 2.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1929248790/Update%20Password%202.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>Scroll down to the <strong>Login Information</strong> section and edit/enter the new Username and/or PIN. Make sure any other required fields are filled out. Once you are satisfied with your changes, click the <strong>Save</strong> button to update your settings.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Update Password 3.png\" width=\"507\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1929248790/Update%20Password%203.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>You can view any changes made to a User Profile by viewing the Change Log at the bottom of the Staff Management page.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Update Password 4.png\" width=\"507\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1929248790/Update%20Password%204.png?api=v2\"></span><hr/><h2 id=\"StaffManagement:UpdateYourUsernameandPassword-ResetYourPassword\">Reset Your Password</h2><p>If you have forgotten your PIN/Password, you can reset your password via an email link.</p><p /><p>Open your web browser and navigate to your store's URL. Your RepairQ URL will be similar to <em>https:businessname.repairq.io</em> or <em>401b-ca1001.repairq.io</em>. On the login screen, click the <strong>&quot;Forgot Password?&quot; </strong>link next to the Login button.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Reset Password 1.png\" width=\"485\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1929248790/Reset%20Password%201.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>Enter the email address associated with your Staff Profile and click <strong>Recover</strong>. You should receive an email with a link to reset your password within a few minutes. If you don't see the email, be sure to check your spam folder. Follow the link and establish a new PIN/Password. Your PIN can be numeric or alphanumeric, based on your preference. After you have established a new PIN, you can log into RepairQ.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Reset Password 2.png\" width=\"314\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1929248790/Reset%20Password%202.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.22.X</p>",
